{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882212430,"sessionID":"ses_2852c116fffet8svsJlHK9NUL6","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad40fa8001WFzfm4qDJ1dgeg","messageID":"msg_d7ad3ffe8001BKZnUxDGxhWUAd","sessionID":"ses_2852c116fffet8svsJlHK9NUL6","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_de525e24110f4014869d19de","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-038/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-038/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-038: Go Unit Tests (workloadmanager) - Tasks\n2: \n3: > **Module:** pkg/workloadmanager\n4: > **Language:** Go\n5: > **Size:** L\n6: > **Status:** ST-3 Completed\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Overview\n11: \n12: This tasks.md defines atomic, independently verifiable tasks for implementing comprehensive Go unit tests for the workloadmanager module. Stage ST-3 (Design) is complete.\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Test File Status\n17: \n18: | Source File | Test File | Status |\n19: |-------------|-----------|--------|\n20: | `service.go` | `service_test.go` | ✅ EXISTS |\n21: | `client.go` | `client_test.go` | ✅ EXISTS |\n22: | `gc.go` | `gc_test.go` | ✅ EXISTS |\n23: | `expiration.go` | `expiration_test.go` | ✅ EXISTS |\n24: | `graceful.go` | `graceful_test.go` | ✅ EXISTS |\n25: | `server.go` | `server_test.go` | ✅ EXISTS |\n26: | `delete_test.go` | `delete_test.go` | ✅ EXISTS |\n27: | `cleanup.go` | `cleanup_test.go` | 🔲 **MISSING** |\n28: | `batch.go` | `batch_test.go` | 🔲 **MISSING** |\n29: | `retry.go` | `retry_test.go` | 🔲 **MISSING** |\n30: | `events.go` | `events_test.go` | 🔲 **MISSING** |\n31: | `reconciler/reconciler.go` | `reconciler/reconciler_test.go` | ✅ EXISTS |\n32: \n33: ---\n34: \n35: ## Tasks\n36: \n37: ### Phase 1: CleanupManager Tests (cleanup_test.go)\n38: \n39: - [ ] **T-101** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/cleanup_test.go`\n40: - [ ] **T-102** Implement AR-038-001-A: `cleanupServices` - deletes orphaned services by owner reference\n41: - [ ] **T-103** Implement AR-038-001-B: `cleanupConfigMaps` - deletes configmaps with auto-delete annotation\n42: - [ ] **T-104** Implement AR-038-001-C: `cleanupPVCs` - handles Retain policy PVCs correctly\n43: - [ ] **T-105** Implement AR-038-001-D: `cleanupOrphanedResources` - cleans services, configmaps, PVCs\n44: - [ ] **T-106** Implement AR-038-001-E: `FindOrphanedServices` - finds services with no owner references\n45: - [ ] **T-107** Implement AR-038-001-F: `CleanupAllResources` - cleans all associated resources\n46: - [ ] **T-108** Add edge case tests: empty namespace, API errors, partial failures\n47: - [ ] **T-109** Verify: All cleanup scenarios pass with fake Kubernetes client\n48: \n49: ### Phase 2: BatchManager Tests (batch_test.go)\n50: \n51: - [ ] **T-201** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/batch_test.go`\n52: - [ ] **T-202** Implement AR-038-002-A: `handleDeleteAllSandboxes` synchronous (≤10 items)\n53: - [ ] **T-203** Implement AR-038-002-B: `handleDeleteAllSandboxes` async (>10 items)\n54: - [ ] **T-204** Implement AR-038-002-C: `handleDeleteByLabelSelector` with label filtering\n55: - [ ] **T-205** Implement AR-038-002-D: `deleteStaleSandboxes` concurrent deletion handling\n56: - [ ] **T-206** Implement AR-038-002-E: BatchManager handles empty results\n57: - [ ] **T-207** Add edge case tests: all deletions fail, partial failures, context cancellation\n58: - [ ] **T-208** Verify: All batch scenarios pass with mock WorkloadManager\n59: \n60: ### Phase 3: Retry Logic Tests (retry_test.go)\n61: \n62: - [ ] **T-301** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/retry_test.go`\n63: - [ ] **T-302** Test `retryDeletion` succeeds on first attempt\n64: - [ ] **T-303** Test `retryDeletion` succeeds after retry\n65: - [ ] **T-304** Test `retryDeletion` fails after max retries\n66: - [ ] **T-305** Test `retryDeletion` respects context cancellation\n67: - [ ] **T-306** Test exponential backoff behavior\n68: - [ ] **T-307** Test backoff ceiling (max 5 seconds)\n69: - [ ] **T-308** Verify: Retry logic handles all error scenarios correctly\n70: \n71: ### Phase 4: EventRecorder Tests (events_test.go)\n72: \n73: - [ ] **T-401** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/events_test.go`\n74: - [ ] **T-402** Test `emitDeletionEvent` creates valid Event objects\n75: - [ ] **T-403** Test event contains correct sandbox metadata\n76: - [ ] **T-404** Test event reason and message formatting\n77: - [ ] **T-405** Test EventRecorder handles API server errors gracefully\n78: - [ ] **T-406** Verify: Events emitted correctly with fake Kubernetes client\n79: \n80: ### Phase 5: Integration & Coverage Verification\n81: \n82: - [ ] **T-501** Run all unit tests: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -v`\n83: - [ ] **T-502** Generate coverage report: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -coverprofile=coverage.out`\n84: - [ ] **T-503** Verify coverage ≥ 70% target\n85: - [ ] **T-504** Add any missing edge case coverage identified in report\n86: - [ ] **T-505** Run `go vet ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n87: - [ ] **T-506** Run `gofmt -s` on all test files\n88: \n89: ---\n90: \n91: ## Test Execution Commands\n92: \n93: ```bash\n94: # Run all tests\n95: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -v\n96: \n97: # Run with coverage\n98: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -coverprofile=coverage.out -covermode=atomic\n99: \n100: # View coverage report\n101: go tool cover -html=coverage.out -o coverage.html\n102: \n103: # Run specific test file\n104: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/cleanup_test.go -v\n105: \n106: # Run tests matching pattern\n107: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run \"TestCleanup\" -v\n108: ```\n109: \n110: ---\n111: \n112: ## Dependencies\n113: \n114: - Go 1.21+\n115: - `testing` package (stdlib)\n116: - `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/fake` for Kubernetes client mocking\n117: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/client/clientset/versioned/fake` for typed client mocking\n118: \n119: ---\n120: \n121: ## Acceptance Criteria\n122: \n123: 1. ✅ All test files created (cleanup_test.go, batch_test.go, retry_test.go, events_test.go)\n124: 2. ✅ All delta-spec scenarios (AR-038-001-A through AR-038-002-E) implemented\n125: 3. ✅ Unit test pass rate: 100%\n126: 4. ✅ Test coverage ≥ 70%\n127: 5. ✅ Code passes `go vet` and `gofmt`\n128: \n129: ---\n130: \n131: ## Notes\n132: \n133: - Size: L - Large change requiring comprehensive testing across multiple modules\n134: - Tests should use table-driven test patterns for parameterized scenarios\n135: - Use fake Kubernetes clientsets to avoid external dependencies\n136: - Each task is independently verifiable and can be completed in any order within a phase\n\n(End of file - total 136 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-038: Go Unit Tests (workloadmanager) - Tasks\n\n> **Module:** pkg/workloadmanager\n> **Language:** Go\n> **Size:** L\n> **Status:** ST-3 Completed\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nThis tasks.md defines atomic, independently verifiable tasks for implementing comprehensive Go unit tests for the workloadmanager module. Stage ST-3 (Design) is complete.\n\n---\n\n## Test File Status\n\n| Source File | Test File | Status |\n|-------------|-----------|--------|\n| `service.go` | `service_test.go` | ✅ EXISTS |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-038/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775882212407,"end":1775882212428}}}}
