{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882215847,"sessionID":"ses_2852c116fffet8svsJlHK9NUL6","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad41d4c001t9IVN3n7O4qG4e","messageID":"msg_d7ad4147f0014FAohHC6iSDrYf","sessionID":"ses_2852c116fffet8svsJlHK9NUL6","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_9cc2489dd7c5439ba9c89f8a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-038/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-038/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-038: Go 单元测试 (workloadmanager)\n2: \n3: ## Summary\n4: \n5: 为 AgentCube 项目的 workloadmanager 模块编写全面的 Go 单元测试，提高代码质量和可维护性。\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Purpose\n10: \n11: ### Background\n12: \n13: workloadmanager 模块是 AgentCube 的核心组件，负责工作负载管理、调度和生命周期管理。该模块管理 `AgentRuntime` 和 `CodeInterpreter` 两种 Kubernetes 自定义资源，处理沙箱的创建、删除、垃圾回收和关联资源清理。当前该模块已有部分测试，但覆盖率和测试深度有待提升。\n14: \n15: ### Goal\n16: \n17: 1. 为 workloadmanager 模块编写全面的单元测试\n18: 2. 提高测试覆盖率到目标水平\n19: 3. 确保关键业务逻辑的测试覆盖\n20: 4. 建立持续测试的基础设施\n21: \n22: ### Value\n23: \n24: - 提高代码质量，减少 regression\n25: - 为重构提供安全网\n26: - 提高开发者信心\n27: - 满足质量门禁要求\n28: \n29: ---\n30: \n31: ## Scope\n32: \n33: ### In-Scope\n34: \n35: - pkg/workloadmanager 下的所有业务逻辑测试\n36: - 关键路径的单元测试\n37: - 边界条件和错误处理测试\n38: - 使用 fake client 进行隔离测试\n39: \n40: ### Out-of-Scope\n41: \n42: - 集成测试\n43: - 性能测试\n44: - E2E 测试\n45: \n46: ---\n47: \n48: ## Acceptance Criteria\n49: \n50: 1. 单元测试通过率 100%\n51: 2. 测试覆盖率目标 ≥ 70%\n52: 3. 所有关键业务逻辑都有对应的测试用例\n53: 4. 测试代码符合 Go 最佳实践\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ## Detailed Scope Analysis\n58: \n59: ### Existing Test Coverage\n60: \n61: | 文件 | 测试文件 | 覆盖率状态 |\n62: |------|----------|------------|\n63: | `types.go` | - | Partial (API response helpers) |\n64: | `service.go` | `service_test.go` | ~70% (CRUD操作已测试, sandbox操作部分覆盖) |\n65: | `batch.go` | - | **0%** |\n66: | `cleanup.go` | - | **0%** |\n67: | `expiration.go` | `expiration_test.go` | Good (isExpired*, shouldExpire*, ExpirationChecker) |\n68: | `gc.go` | `gc_test.go` | Good (GCWorker lifecycle, expiration checks) |\n69: | `graceful.go` | `graceful_test.go` | Good (connection tracking, draining) |\n70: | `retry.go` | - | **0%** |\n71: | `events.go` | - | **0%** |\n72: | `server.go` | `server_test.go` | Partial (basic HTTP handlers) |\n73: | `client.go` | `client_test.go` | Good (client creation, path expansion) |\n74: | `reconciler/reconciler.go` | `reconciler_test.go` | Partial |\n75: \n76: ### Components Requiring Additional Tests\n77: \n78: #### 1. `batch.go` - BatchManager\n79: - `handleDeleteAllSandboxes()`: async deletion threshold (AsyncThreshold=10)\n80: - `handleDeleteByLabelSelector()`: label-based deletion\n81: - `deleteStaleSandboxes()`: stale sandbox cleanup with concurrent deletion\n82: \n83: #### 2. `cleanup.go` - CleanupManager\n84: - `cleanupServices()`: service owner reference matching\n85: - `cleanupConfigMaps()`: configmap auto-delete annotation handling (agentcube.volcano.sh/auto-delete)\n86: - `cleanupPVCs()`: PVC retain policy logic (PersistentVolumeReclaimRetain)\n87: - `cleanupOrphanedResources()`: orchestration of cleanup operations\n88: - `CleanupAllResources()`: full resource cleanup\n89: - `FindOrphanedServices()`: orphaned service detection\n90: \n91: #### 3. `retry.go` - Retry Logic\n92: - `retryDeletion()`: retry with exponential backoff\n93: - `retryWithBackoff()`: configurable retry with backoff\n94: - `WithRetry()`: public retry wrapper\n95: - `IsTransientError()`: transient error detection (注意: 有bug - 始终返回true)\n96: \n97: #### 4. `events.go` - EventRecorder\n98: - `emitDeletionEvent()`: Kubernetes event emission\n99: - Various event type methods (TTL, Idle, MaxLifetime, Stale)\n100: - `sendDeletionWebhook()`: webhook HTTP client with retry logic\n101: - `logDeletionAudit()`: audit logging\n102: - `LogDeletionComplete()`: completion logging\n103: \n104: #### 5. Additional Coverage for `service.go`\n105: - `DeleteSandbox()`: sandbox deletion by session ID\n106: - `GetSandboxBySessionID()`: sandbox lookup\n107: - `ListSandboxes()`: combined listing from both AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter\n108: - `sandboxFromAgentRuntime()`: conversion function\n109: - `sandboxFromCodeInterpreter()`: conversion function\n110: \n111: ---\n112: \n113: ## Impact Analysis\n114: \n115: ### Benefits\n116: \n117: 1. **Increased Reliability**: Comprehensive test coverage reduces regression risk\n118: 2. **Bug Detection**: Tests for `IsTransientError()` will catch the existing bug\n119: 3. **Safe Refactoring**: Batch deletion and cleanup operations can be safely modified\n120: 4. **Documentation**: Tests serve as executable documentation\n121: 5. **CI Confidence**: Full test suite enables confident continuous integration\n122: \n123: ### Risks\n124: \n125: 1. **Fake Client Complexity**: Testing `cleanup.go` and `events.go` requires extensive fake k8s client setup\n126: 2. **Timing Sensitivity**: `retry.go` tests involve timing-dependent behavior\n127: 3. **HTTP Mocking**: `sendDeletionWebhook()` requires HTTP handler mocking\n128: \n129: ### Estimated Test Files\n130: \n131: - `batch_test.go` (new, ~150 lines)\n132: - `cleanup_test.go` (new, ~200 lines)\n133: - `retry_test.go` (new, ~100 lines)\n134: - `events_test.go` (new, ~150 lines)\n135: - `service_test.go` (enhance, ~100 additional lines)\n136: \n137: ---\n138: \n139: ## Alternatives Considered\n140: \n141: ### 1. Integration Tests with Real Kubernetes Cluster\n142: \n143: - **Pros**: Tests actual behavior, no fake setup needed\n144: - **Cons**: Requires cluster access, slower, harder to CI\n145: - **Verdict**: Not preferred for unit tests\n146: \n147: ### 2. Table-Driven Tests\n148: \n149: - **Pros**: Comprehensive edge case coverage, easy to extend\n150: - **Cons**: Can become verbose for complex scenarios\n151: - **Verdict**: Use for simple functions (retry, expiration)\n152: \n153: ### 3. Property-Based Testing\n154: \n155: - **Pros**: Discovers edge cases automatically\n156: - **Cons**: Requires additional library, higher complexity\n157: - **Verdict**: Not needed for this module\n158: \n159: ### 4. Mock Libraries (testify/mock, gomock)\n160: \n161: - **Pros**: Cleaner mock setup, verification methods\n162: - **Cons**: Additional dependency\n163: - **Verdict**: Use manual fakes where possible (consistent with existing code)\n164: \n165: ---\n166: \n167: ## Implementation Plan\n168: \n169: 1. **Phase 1**: `retry_test.go` - Simple, foundational\n170: 2. **Phase 2**: `batch_test.go` - Uses existing WorkloadManager interface\n171: 3. **Phase 3**: `cleanup_test.go` - Requires k8s fake client setup\n172: 4. **Phase 4**: `events_test.go` - Requires k8s fake client and HTTP mocking\n173: 5. **Phase 5**: Enhance `service_test.go` - Sandbox operation coverage\n\n(End of file - total 173 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-038: Go 单元测试 (workloadmanager)\n\n## Summary\n\n为 AgentCube 项目的 workloadmanager 模块编写全面的 Go 单元测试，提高代码质量和可维护性。\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nworkloadmanager 模块是 AgentCube 的核心组件，负责工作负载管理、调度和生命周期管理。该模块管理 `AgentRuntime` 和 `CodeInterpreter` 两种 Kubernetes 自定义资源，处理沙箱的创建、删除、垃圾回收和关联资源清理。当前该模块已有部分测试，但覆盖率和测试深度有待提升。\n\n### Goal\n\n1. 为 workloadmanager 模块编写全面的单元测试\n2. 提高测试覆盖率到目标水平\n3. 确保关键业务逻辑的测试覆盖\n4. 建立持续测试的基础设施","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-038/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775882215829,"end":1775882215845}}}}
